    "recap_headline": "University of North Florida",
    "recap_text": "JACKSONVILLE, Fla.\n\u2013 Junior infielder\nMathew Farner\nbelted a two-run walk-off home run in the bottom of the ninth to propel North Florida Baseball to a sweep over FGCU, 6-4, in Game 3 of the series at Harmon Stadium on Sunday.\nNorth Florida improves to 5-1 in ASUN Conference play, the best record in the conference through the first two weekends, to lead the Graphite Division.\nNorth Florida stormed back from a 4-1 deficit in the fourth inning with two runs in the sixth, one in the seventh and two in the ninth.\nAfter FGCU led 3-0, redshirt junior utility player\nJackson Toberman\ndrove in North Florida's first run of the game with an RBI single in the bottom of the third. Florida Gulf Coast extended its lead to 4-1 in the fourth inning.\nFreshman infielder\nDrew Buchanan\ndelivered a clutch two-RBI single to bring North Florida within one run of FGCU in the bottom of the sixth inning. Redshirt junior utility player\nBoone Hosey\ntied the game with a sacrifice fly in the bottom of the seventh inning.\nAfter a leadoff single from junior infielder\nMitchell Collins\n, Farner\u00a0came up in the bottom of the ninth and notched the walk-off homer to secure the series sweep.\nNORTH FLORIDA 6, FGCU 4\nPitchers of Record\nWin:\nDevin Diggs\n(2-0)\nLoss:\nAshton Pocol (3-3)\nLine Scores\nNORTH FLORIDA\n| 6 R, 8 H, 0 E\nFGCU\n| 4 R, 7 H, 2 E\nStatistical Leaders\nNORTH FLORIDA\nMathew Farner\n| 1-4, 2 RBI, 1 HR, 1 R\nDrew Buchanan\n| 1-3, 2 RBI, 1 R\nFGCU\nJavier Gorostola | 2-4, 2 RBI, 2 R\nUP NEXT\nNorth Florida travels for its away series of the River City Rumble at Jacksonville on Friday, March 27 at 7 p.m. ET.",
